Patch Set 2:

> If the backend cert doesn't have the SANs included, how does it work in our CI, where we have kolla_verify_tls_backend set to yes?

I've found why invalid certificates work on CI. This is because them verified only against CA. Both subject and subjectAlternateNames attributes not verified with only 'verify required' option set. http://cbonte.github.io/haproxy-dconv/1.8/configuration.html#5.2-verify
